FBIS3-30115 "dreas038_a_94021" FBIS-EAS-94-038 Document Type:Daily Report 25 February 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan UN Asks Tokyo To Send Observers to El Salvador OW2502095294 Tokyo KYODO in English 0843 GMT 25 Feb 94 OW2502095294 Tokyo KYODO Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Tokyo, Feb. 25 KYODO -- The United Nations has formally requested Japan to send 15 election observers to El Salvador to join a UN team to monitor the March parliamentary elections, the Foreign Ministry said Friday [25 February]. Japan received a written request on the matter from UN Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali, the ministry said. The government will study the situation in various fields in El Salvador before deciding to send the election monitors, it said. Salvadoran President Alfredo Felix Cristiani, during his visit to Japan in November, asked Japan to send election monitors for the March poll.
